951	### 2.1 Anatomy Part Reference
952	
953	| Part                | Element                   | Key Attributes                                                                                                   |
954	| ------------------- | ------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
955	| `Root`              | `<div>`                   | `data-ars-scope="table"` `data-ars-part="root"`                                                                  |
956	| `Table`             | `<table>`                 | `role="grid"` (interactive) or `role="table"`                                                                    |
957	| `Caption`           | `<caption>`               | `id` wired to table `aria-labelledby`                                                                            |
958	| `Head`              | `<thead>`                 | `data-ars-sticky` when `sticky_header`                                                                           |
959	| `Body`              | `<tbody>`                 | —                                                                                                                |
960	| `Foot`              | `<tfoot>`                 | —                                                                                                                |
961	| `Row`               | `<tr>`                    | `aria-selected`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-disabled`, `data-ars-selected`, `data-ars-expanded`, `data-ars-disabled` |
962	| `ColumnHeader`      | `<th scope="col">`        | `aria-sort`, `data-ars-sort`, `data-ars-sorted`                                                                  |
963	| `RowHeader`         | `<th scope="row">`        | —                                                                                                                |
964	| `Cell`              | `<td>`                    | `tabindex` managed for grid nav                                                                                  |
965	| `SelectAllCheckbox` | `<input type="checkbox">` | `aria-label`, `aria-checked` (incl. mixed)                                                                       |
966	| `RowCheckbox`       | `<input type="checkbox">` | `aria-label`, `aria-checked`                                                                                     |
967	| `ExpandTrigger`     | `<button>`                | `aria-expanded`, `data-ars-expanded`                                                                             |
968	| `ExpandedContent`   | `<tr>` + inner `<td>`     | `hidden` when collapsed, `data-ars-expanded`                                                                     |
969	
970	### 2.2 Expandable Row Anatomy
971	
972	Tables may support expandable rows that reveal additional detail content:
973	
974	- **Expand Trigger**: Each expandable row includes a toggle button (typically a chevron icon) as the first cell or as an overlay on the row. The trigger receives `aria-expanded="true|false"` reflecting the current state. The trigger button MUST also set `aria-controls` pointing to the `id` of the detail row so assistive technology can navigate directly to the expanded content.
975	- **Content Area**: Expanded content is rendered as a full-width `<td colspan="...">` (spanning all columns) inside a `<tr>` immediately below the parent row.
976	- **Toggle Anatomy**: The expand/collapse control is a `<button>` element with `aria-label` describing the action (e.g., "Expand row" / "Collapse row"), managed via the `Messages` i18n struct.
977	
978	#### 2.2.1 Nesting Rules
979	
980	- **Single-level expansion only**: Expandable rows support one level of expansion. A row can expand to show detail content, but the detail content MUST NOT itself contain expandable rows. Nested expansion introduces unpredictable keyboard navigation and screen reader confusion.
981	- **Hierarchical data**: For tree-structured or multi-level hierarchical data, use the `TreeView` component instead of nested table expansion. TreeView provides proper `aria-level`, `aria-setsize`, and `aria-posinset` attributes for arbitrary nesting depth.
982	- **Indentation Level**: Since expansion is single-level, `aria-level` attributes are not used on expandable rows. All data rows are at the same level; expanded content is supplementary detail, not a child row.
983	
984	## 3. Accessibility
985	
986	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
987	
988	- **role="grid"** when `interactive=true`; **role="table"** otherwise.
989	- Sortable `ColumnHeader`: `aria-sort="ascending|descending|none"`. Enter/Space toggles sort.
990	- `Row`: `aria-selected` present only when `selection_mode != None`.
991	- `Row` with expand: `aria-expanded="true|false"`.
992	- `SelectAllCheckbox`: `aria-checked="mixed"` (indeterminate) when a subset of rows selected.
993	
994	**`aria-sort` and `aria-current` Semantics**
995	
996	- Sortable column headers MUST set `aria-sort` to one of: `"ascending"`, `"descending"`, or `"none"`.
997	- When a column is not currently sorted, set `aria-sort="none"` (not omitted) so screen readers can distinguish sortable from non-sortable columns.
998	- When sort state changes (user clicks a column header), announce the new sort state via `LiveAnnouncer` with `Politeness::Polite`: e.g., `"Sorted by Name, ascending"`. Use the `Messages.sort_ascending` / `Messages.sort_descending` message keys.
